\begin_layout Plain Layout
Change 1)these are the guesses from GPOPS!!! The MINVO (left) is guaranteed
 to be the smallest (irregular) tethraedron that encloses the 
\begin_inset Formula $3^{rd}$
\end_inset

-order polynomial curve in red.
 On the right, the simplex found using the Bezier Basis.
 The ratio between the two volumes is guaranteed to be 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{V_{MINVO}}{V_{Berns}}\approx0.4237$
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:comparison3d"

\end_inset

 for any 
\begin_inset Formula $3^{rd}$
\end_inset

-order polynomial curve.
\end_layout

