\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

-simplex
\series default
: Convex hull of 
\begin_inset Formula $n+1$
\end_inset

 points 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{v}_{0},...,\boldsymbol{v}_{n}\in\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

.
 We will use the letter 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 to denote a simplex, and we will denote the set of all possible 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

-simplexes as 
\begin_inset Formula $S^{n}$
\end_inset

.
 The points 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{v}_{0},...,\boldsymbol{v}_{n}\in\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

 are called the vertexes of the simplex.
 Let us also define the matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{V}:=\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
\boldsymbol{v}_{0} & \cdots & \boldsymbol{v}_{n}\end{array}\right]$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace 0.2cm
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Box Boxed
position "t"
hor_pos "c"
has_inner_box 1
inner_pos "t"
use_parbox 0
use_makebox 0
width "100col%"
special "none"
height "1in"
height_special "totalheight"
thickness "0.4pt"
separation "3pt"
shadowsize "4pt"
framecolor "black"
backgroundcolor "none"
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
Polynomial curve
\series default
 
\series bold
of degree
\series default
 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 
\series bold
and dimension
\series default
 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

: Parametric curve 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{p}(t):=\left[\begin{array}{c}
p_{0}(t)\\
\vdots\\
p_{k-1}(t)
\end{array}\right]:=\boldsymbol{P}\boldsymbol{t}=\sum_{j=0}^{n}\boldsymbol{p}_{j}t^{j}=\left[\begin{array}{c}
\boldsymbol{c}_{0}^{T}\boldsymbol{t}\\
\vdots\\
\boldsymbol{c}_{k-1}^{T}\boldsymbol{t}
\end{array}\right]$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{i}(t)=\boldsymbol{c}_{i}^{T}\boldsymbol{t}$
\end_inset

 is a polynomial of degree 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
p_{i}(t)=\sum_{j=0}^{n}p_{i,j}t^{j}=\boldsymbol{p}_{i}^{T}\boldsymbol{t},\qquad c_{i,j}\in\mathbb{R},t\in\mathbb{R}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

In this paper, we will use the polynomial curves of the form 
\begin_inset Formula $k=n$
\end_inset

 and we will refer to them simply as 
\begin_inset Formula $n-$
\end_inset

th order polyomial curve.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{P}$
\end_inset

 will denote the matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{P}:=\left[\begin{array}{c}
\boldsymbol{c}_{0}^{T}\\
\vdots\\
\boldsymbol{c}_{k-1}^{T}
\end{array}\right]_{k\times n}\equiv\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
\boldsymbol{p}_{n} & \cdots & \boldsymbol{p}_{0}\end{array}\right]_{k\times n}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{t}:=\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
t^{n} & t^{n-1}\cdots & 1\end{array}\right]^{T}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace 0.2cm
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let us also define the permutation matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $Q=\left[\begin{array}{cccc}
0 & \cdots & 0 & 1\\
0 & \cdots & 1 & 0\\
\vdots & \iddots & \vdots & \vdots\\
1 & 0 & 0 & 0
\end{array}\right]$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Problem definition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This project investigates the two following problems:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace 0.2cm
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Box Boxed
position "t"
hor_pos "c"
has_inner_box 1
inner_pos "t"
