\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
Problem 1
\series default
: Given an 
\begin_inset Formula $n-$
\end_inset

th order polyomial curve 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{p}(t)$
\end_inset

, find the 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

-simplex 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 with minimum volume that contains 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{p}(t)$
\end_inset

.
 In other words:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\min_{S\in S^{n}}\quad f_{1}:=vol(S)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{array}{cc}
s.t. & \boldsymbol{p}(t)\in S\quad\forall t\in[-1,1]\end{array}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace 0.2cm
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For instance, for 
\begin_inset Formula $n=2$
\end_inset

, this problem tries to find the triangle with the smallest area that contains
 the curve 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\begin{array}{cc}
x(t) & y(t)\end{array}\right]^{T}$
\end_inset

 , where 
\begin_inset Formula $x(t)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y(t)$
\end_inset

 are 
\begin_inset Formula $2^{nd}$
\end_inset

-deg polynomials.
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $n=3$
\end_inset

, it tries to find the tetrahedron with the smallest volume that contains
 the curve 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
x(t) & y(t) & z(t)\end{array}\right]^{T}$
\end_inset

(all 
\begin_inset Formula $3^{rd}$
\end_inset

-deg polynomials).
 And so on.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As we will prove later in the report, problem 1 is closely connected to
 the following problem: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace 0.2cm
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Box Boxed
position "t"
hor_pos "c"
has_inner_box 1
inner_pos "t"
use_parbox 0
use_makebox 0
width "100col%"
special "none"
height "1in"
height_special "totalheight"
thickness "0.4pt"
separation "3pt"
shadowsize "4pt"
framecolor "black"
backgroundcolor "none"
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
Problem 
\series default
2: Given the vertexes 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{v}_{0},...,\boldsymbol{v}_{n}$
\end_inset

 of an 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

-simplex 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

, find the 
\begin_inset Formula $n-$
\end_inset

th order polyomial curve 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{p}(t)$
\end_inset

 contained in 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

, whose coefficients vectors 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{p}_{n},...,\boldsymbol{p}_{1}$
\end_inset

 span a paralellogram with largest volume.
 In other words:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\max_{\boldsymbol{p}(t)}\quad f_{2}:=\left|\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
\boldsymbol{p}_{n} & \cdots & \boldsymbol{p}_{1}\end{array}\right]\right|=\left|\left[\begin{array}{c}
\boldsymbol{P}\\
\boldsymbol{e}^{T}
\end{array}\right]\right|
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{array}{cc}
s.t. & \boldsymbol{p}(t)\in S:=conv(\{\boldsymbol{v}_{0},...,\boldsymbol{v}_{n}\})\quad\forall t\in[-1,1]\end{array}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

