\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Results obtained for the MINVO basis, and the matrices using the Bernstein
 basis.
 Each polynomial in the basis is given by the rows of 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{A}\boldsymbol{t}$
\end_inset

, with 
\begin_inset Formula $t\in[-1,1]$
\end_inset

.
 The bigger the absolute value of the determinant, the smaller the associated
 simplex 
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "tab:table_matrices"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Conversion from Bezier to MINVO
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Define 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{A}:=\left[\begin{array}{c}
\boldsymbol{\lambda}_{1}^{T}\\
\boldsymbol{\lambda}_{2}^{T}\\
\boldsymbol{\lambda}_{3}^{T}
\end{array}\right]_{3\times3}$
\end_inset

 , 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{t}:=\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
t^{2} & t & 1\end{array}\right]^{T}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{i}(t):=\boldsymbol{\lambda}_{i}^{T}\boldsymbol{t}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{1}$
\end_inset

 the vector of ones.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Box Boxed
position "t"
hor_pos "c"
has_inner_box 1
inner_pos "t"
use_parbox 0
use_makebox 0
width "100col%"
special "none"
height "1in"
height_special "totalheight"
thickness "0.4pt"
separation "3pt"
shadowsize "4pt"
framecolor "black"
backgroundcolor "none"
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
Problem
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\max_{\boldsymbol{A}\in\mathbb{R}^{3\times3}}\quad\left|\boldsymbol{A}\right|
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{array}{cc}
s.t. & \lambda_{i}(t)\ge0\quad\forall t\in[-1,1],\;\;\forall i\\
 & \sum\lambda_{i}(t)=1\quad\forall t\in[-1,1]
\end{array}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All the local minima found satisfy 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{1}(t)=\lambda_{3}(-t)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{2}(t)=\lambda_{2}(-t)$
\end_inset

.
 What's the formal proof to show that that is the case? (I'd like to impose
 it as a constraint, as it would allow me to reduce the number of variables,
 specially when 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{A}$
\end_inset

 is quite big)
\end_layout

