\begin_layout Section
Conclusions and Future Work
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This work derived and presented MINVO, a polynomial basis that .
 The key features
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The exciting results of this project can naturally lead to the following
 questions:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Does there exist a closed-form solution for any degree 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Does there exist a recursivity formula to obtain the solution of problem
 3 for 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 given the previous solutions 
\begin_inset Formula $1:n-1$
\end_inset

? Will this recursivity formula allow to easily prove global optimality
 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Conclusions and Future Work
\end_layout

